a G; Meyers, Marc A; Meyers (2009). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120402203544/http://www.meyersgroup.ucsd.edu/papers/journals/Meyers%20326.pdf">"Toucan and hornbill beaks: A comparative study"</a> <span style="font-size:85%;">(PDF)</span>. <i>Acta Biomaterialia</i>. <b>6</b> (2): 331–343. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.actbio.2009.08.026">10.1016/j.actbio.2009.08.026</a>. <a href="/wiki/PubMed_Identifier" class="mw-redirect" title="PubMed Identifier">PMID</a>&#160;<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19699818">19699818</a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.meyersgroup.ucsd.edu/papers/journals/Meyers%20326.pdf">the original</a> <span style="font-size:85%;">(PDF)</span> on 2012-04-02.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Acta+Biomaterialia&amp;rft.atitle=Toucan+and+hornbill+beaks%3A+A+comparative+study&amp;rft.volume=6&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=331-343&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2Fj.actbio.2009.08.026&amp;rft_id=info%3Apmid%2F19699818&amp;rft.aulast=Seki&amp;rft.aufirst=Yasuaki&amp;rft.au=Bodde%2C+Sara+G&amp;rft.au=Meyers%2C+Marc+A&amp;rft.au=Meyers&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.meyersgroup.ucsd.edu%2Fpapers%2Fjournals%2FMeyers%2520326.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABeak" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li> <li id="cite_note-7"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://sicb.org/meetings/2012/schedule/abstractdetails.php?id=542">Beyond the Beak: Modeling avian cranial kinesis and the evolution of bird skull shapes</a></span></li> <li id="cite_note-Gill148-8"><span class="mw-cite-backlink">^ <a href="#cite_ref-Gill148_8-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-Gill148_8-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class="reference-text">Gill (1995), p. 148.</span></li> <li id="cite_note-9"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-9">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation journal">Mayr, Gerald (2005). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.senckenberg.de/files/content/forschung/abteilung/terrzool/ornithologie/chascacocolius.pdf">"A new eocene Chascacocolius-like mousebird (Aves: Coliiformes) with a remarkable gaping adaptation"</a> <span style="font-size:85%;">(PDF)</span>. <i>Organisms, Diversity &amp; Evolution</i>. <b>5</b>: 167–171. <a href="/wiki/Digital_object_identifier" title="Digital object identifier">doi</a>:<a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="//doi.org/10.1016%2Fj.ode.2004.10.013">10.1016/j.ode.2004.10.013</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Organisms%2C+Diversity+%26+Evolution&amp;rft.atitle=A+new+eocene+Chascacocolius-like+mousebird+%28Aves%3A+Coliiformes%29+with+a+remarkable+gaping+adaptation&amp;rft.volume=5&amp;rft.pages=167-171&amp;rft.date=2005&amp;rft_id=info%3Adoi%2F10.1016%2Fj.ode.2004.10.013&amp;rft.au=Mayr%2C+Gerald&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.senckenberg.de%2Ffiles%2Fcontent%2Fforschung%2Fabteilung%2Fterrzool%2Fornithologie%2Fchascacocolius.pdf&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ABeak" class="Z3988"><span style="display:none;">&#160;</span></span></span></li> <li id="cite_note-10"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-10">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite class="citation book">Kaiser, Gary W. (2007). <i>The Inner Bird: Anatomy and Evolution</i>. Vancouver, BC: UBC Press. p.&#160;19. <a href="/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book